Inflammatory pseudotumor of the pancreas resembling pancreatic cancer: clinical, diagnostic and therapeutic considerations. Pancreatic masses could be malignant or benign. Among these latter inflammatory pseudotumor is an uncommon mass rarely located in the pancreas and it must be considered in differential diagnosis with pancreatic cancer. A case report and literature review of inflammatory pseudotumor were recognized to well known this rare pathology regarding its clinical, diagnostic, therapeutic and histopathological feature. Twenty-one cases of inflammatory pseudotumor in the adult were reviewed from the literature 10 (47.6%) were female, 11 (52.3%) male